Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves. Crumble the @feta cheese{100}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all).

In a #large bowl{} mix together the @olive oil for the dressing{2} with the @red wine vinegar{12}, a @sugar{pinch} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large frying pan{} over high heat. Add the @diced chicken thigh{210}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir fry until heated through, ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the @zhoug style paste{50} with half the tomatoes and cook for a further ~{1%minute}until piping hot.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain naans{2} on a #baking tray{} and bake for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the lettuce and remaining tomatoes to the bowl with the dressing and toss to coat. Pop the naans onto plates, divide the @mayonnaise{32} between them and spread with the back of a #spoon{}. Top with the zhoug chicken, scatter over the feta and coriander. Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!